{
  "texts": [
    "However, as the dataset size diminishes, the difference in performance between models with and without pretraining becomes increasingly significant, underscoring the value of pretraining when fine-tuning with a limited amount of data.",
    "The Pareto fronts (Fig. 5e) of validity versus uniqueness at a small data number (50 data only) further prove the model with pretraining shows a consistently better performance.",
    "Finally, we reveal that pretraining enhances the model's capacity to capture the polymer characteristics of fine-tuning dataset (HTP-MD dataset), while also producing a diverse range of polymers during the generation, as evidenced by improved similarity and diversity metrics.",
    "The improvement is always evident regardless of the number of training data (Fig. 5d).",
    "The diverse polymer structures and rich chemical information in the PI1M dataset underpin the superior performance achieved through pretraining."
  ]
}